VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?:exec|system|run|sh\s+-c)\s+[^"'][^;|\n]*\$\w
WHEN EXPR MISSING:"\"$|'$|shellcheck\s+disable|# shellcheck && MISSING:test\s+-z|test\s+-n|\[\s*-z|\[\s*-n
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects unquoted variables passed to shell execution contexts.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Unquoted Variable in Command Context.
